{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0164aK6oDmrKfJevyDT9AC5k","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# TEAMMEM Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine Rust contracts for team memory sync with mandatory security checks (path validation + secret scanning) and deterministic conflict handling.\n6\t\n7\t## 2. Evidence from Current Code\n8\t\n9\t1. `setup.ts:365` startup gate for TEAMMEM watcher.\n10\t2. `services/teamMemorySync/watcher.ts:253` watcher start conditions.\n11\t3. `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:177` Bearer auth usage.\n12\t4. `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:496` conflict handling (412).\n13\t5. `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:741` mkdir + write path.\n14\t6. `services/teamMemorySync/secretScanner.ts` client-side secret scanner.\n15\t7. `services/teamMemorySync/teamMemSecretGuard.ts` write-time secret guard.\n16\t8. `memdir/teamMemPaths.ts` path validation and traversal protection.\n17\t\n18\t## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n19\t\n20\t1. `crates/api-types`: sync requests/results, conflict and secret-scan outcomes.\n21\t2. `crates/app-services`: sync orchestration and retry policy.\n22\t3. `crates/state-store`: local read/merge/write abstraction.\n23\t4. `crates/remote-runtime`: sync endpoint client and auth integration.\n24\t5. `crates/platform`: secure path validation and filesystem adapters.\n25\t6. `crates/config`: retry cap, max-size/max-entry defaults.\n26\t\n27\t## 4. Core Contracts (Rust Sketch)\n28\t\n29\t```rust\n30\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n31\tpub struct TeamMemSyncOptions {\n32\t    pub max_retries: u8,\n33\t    pub max_file_size_bytes: usize,\n34\t    pub max_entries: Option<usize>,\n35\t}\n36\t\n37\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n38\tpub struct SecretScanFinding { pub rule_id: String, pub label: String }\n39\t\n40\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n41\tpub struct SyncResult {\n42\t    pub files_pulled: usize,\n43\t    pub files_pushed: usize,\n44\t    pub skipped_secrets: Vec<String>,\n45\t}\n46\t\n47\t#[async_trait::async_trait]\n48\tpub trait TeamMemorySyncService {\n49\t    async fn pull(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n50\t    async fn push(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n51\t    async fn sync(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n52\t}\n53\t```\n54\t\n55\t## 5. Error Taxonomy\n56\t\n57\t1. `AuthUnavailable`\n58\t2. `Unauthorized`\n59\t3. `ConflictExhausted`\n60\t4. `PathValidationFailed`\n61\t5. `SecretDetected`\n62\t6. `FileTooLarge`\n63\t7. `EntryLimitExceeded`\n64\t8. `StorageWriteError`\n65\t9. `UpstreamTimeout`\n66\t\n67\t## 6. Policy Rules\n68\t\n69\t1. All remote writes pass secret scan first.\n70\t2. All local writes pass canonical path validation first.\n71\t3. 412 conflict uses bounded retry with deterministic terminal error.\n72\t4. Files over max-size are skipped with explicit classification.\n73\t5. Max-entry overflow has deterministic truncation/skip policy.\n74\t\n75\t## 7. Constants Classification\n76\t\n77\t1. `api-types`: sync outcome enums and error class identifiers.\n78\t2. `config`: retry caps, limits, endpoint keys.\n79\t3. `core-domain`: invariant ordering (validate -> scan -> write/push).\n80\t4. `state-store`/`platform`: local lock/key/file internals.\n81\t5. `ui-tui`: user-facing summaries only.\n82\t\n83\t## 8. Acceptance Matrix\n84\t\n85\t### Contract tests\n86\t\n87\t1. Path traversal/symlink escape returns `PathValidationFailed`.\n88\t2. Secret findings skip file and never return raw secret content.\n89\t3. 412 conflicts stop at configured max retries.\n90\t\n91\t### Integration tests\n92\t\n93\t1. Pull -> merge -> push happy path with ETag handling.\n94\t2. Unauthorized token maps to stable auth error class.\n95\t3. Mixed payload with oversized + secret + valid entries behaves deterministically.\n96\t\n97\t### Security tests\n98\t\n99\t1. Secret scanner redaction path verified.\n100\t2. Write outside team root prevented.\n101\t3. Audit events emitted for skipped secrets and conflicts.\n102\t\n103\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013MtP5ZHyjqKA1pJYvyhzVM","session_id":"b9e339b7-1479-46b1-b285-3ad36d9e4141","uuid":"413c2c9c-4728-43aa-96b9-347a29ef417f","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:38:51.765Z"}
