{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015fDMBUNGaqDyPg6ehS7GSX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# BRIDGE_MODE / CCR Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine a production-grade Rust contract for Remote Control (BRIDGE_MODE / CCR) that preserves current behavior while enforcing clearer boundaries.\n6\t\n7\tPrimary evidence in current code:\n8\t\n9\t1. Entitlement/gate logic: `bridge/bridgeEnabled.ts`\n10\t2. Session lifecycle API: `bridge/createSession.ts`\n11\t3. Session ID compatibility shim: `bridge/sessionIdCompat.ts`\n12\t4. Runtime protocol types and dependencies: `bridge/types.ts`\n13\t5. Command entry path and bridge wiring: `entrypoints/cli.tsx:112`\n14\t6. Session archive and shutdown behavior: `bridge/createSession.ts:263`\n15\t\n16\t## 2. Rust Ownership Boundaries\n17\t\n18\t### Crate mapping\n19\t\n20\t1. `crates/api-types`\n21\tPurpose: shared wire/domain contracts for remote sessions.\n22\t\n23\t2. `crates/app-services`\n24\tPurpose: policy and orchestration (gate behavior, retry policy, archive guarantees, resume semantics).\n25\t\n26\t3. `crates/remote-runtime`\n27\tPurpose: concrete CCR client implementation (HTTP transport, auth headers, compat session ID translation).\n28\t\n29\t4. `crates/config`\n30\tPurpose: feature gate keys, default timeouts, environment variable names.\n31\t\n32\t5. `bins/app-cli`\n33\tPurpose: user-facing command entry and message rendering only.\n34\t\n35\t### Architectural rule\n36\t\n37\t`app-cli -> app-services -> remote-runtime -> platform`\n38\t\n39\t`app-services` owns policy decisions. `remote-runtime` must not decide fail-open/fail-close behavior.\n40\t\n41\t## 3. Proposed Contracts (Rust)\n42\t\n43\t### 3.1 API types (`crates/api-types/src/remote_session.rs`)\n44\t\n45\t```rust\n46\tuse serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\n47\tuse std::time::Duration;\n48\t\n49\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Eq)]\n50\tpub struct RemoteSessionId(pub String);\n51\t\n52\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Eq)]\n53\tpub struct EnvironmentId(pub String);\n54\t\n55\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Eq)]\n56\tpub enum RemoteSessionState {\n57\t    Pending,\n58\t    Running,\n59\t    Idle,\n60\t    RequiresAction,\n61\t    Archived,\n62\t    Expired,\n63\t    Failed,\n64\t}\n65\t\n66\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n67\tpub struct CreateRemoteSessionRequest {\n68\t    pub environment_id: EnvironmentId,\n69\t    pub title: Option<String>,\n70\t    pub permission_mode: Option<String>,\n71\t    pub events: Vec<SessionEvent>,\n72\t}\n73\t\n74\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n75\tpub struct SessionEvent {\n76\t    pub event_type: String,\n77\t    pub payload_json: serde_json::Value,\n78\t}\n79\t\n80\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013MtP5ZHyjqKA1pJYvyhzVM","session_id":"b9e339b7-1479-46b1-b285-3ad36d9e4141","uuid":"cd4b5ab4-53c0-456b-bfc5-be8313f8fa2d","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:39:15.200Z"}
