{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013MtP5ZHyjqKA1pJYvyhzVM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE TEAMMEM SYSTEM EXPLORATION REPORT\n\n---\n\n### 1. TEAMMEM-CONTRACT.MD FILE\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/teammem-contract.md`\n\n**Full Contents:**\n\nThe contract defines Rust bindings for team memory sync with mandatory security checks. Key sections:\n\n- **Objective:** Define Rust contracts for team memory sync with mandatory security checks (path validation + secret scanning) and deterministic conflict handling.\n\n- **Evidence from Current Code:**\n  - `setup.ts:365` startup gate for TEAMMEM watcher\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/watcher.ts:253` watcher start conditions\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:177` Bearer auth usage\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:496` conflict handling (412)\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:741` mkdir + write path\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/secretScanner.ts` client-side secret scanner\n  - `services/teamMemorySync/teamMemSecretGuard.ts` write-time secret guard\n  - `memdir/teamMemPaths.ts` path validation and traversal protection\n\n- **Rust Boundary Mapping:**\n  - `crates/api-types`: sync requests/results, conflict and secret-scan outcomes\n  - `crates/app-services`: sync orchestration and retry policy\n  - `crates/state-store`: local read/merge/write abstraction\n  - `crates/remote-runtime`: sync endpoint client and auth integration\n  - `crates/platform`: secure path validation and filesystem adapters\n  - `crates/config`: retry cap, max-size/max-entry defaults\n\n- **Core Contracts (Rust Sketch):**\n  ```rust\n  #[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n  pub struct TeamMemSyncOptions {\n      pub max_retries: u8,\n      pub max_file_size_bytes: usize,\n      pub max_entries: Option<usize>,\n  }\n  \n  #[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n  pub struct SecretScanFinding { pub rule_id: String, pub label: String }\n  \n  #[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n  pub struct SyncResult {\n      pub files_pulled: usize,\n      pub files_pushed: usize,\n      pub skipped_secrets: Vec<String>,\n  }\n  \n  #[async_trait::async_trait]\n  pub trait TeamMemorySyncService {\n      async fn pull(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n      async fn push(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n      async fn sync(&self) -> Result<SyncResult, TeamMemError>;\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Error Taxonomy:** AuthUnavailable, Unauthorized, ConflictExhausted, PathValidationFailed, SecretDetected, FileTooLarge, EntryLimitExceeded, StorageWriteError, UpstreamTimeout\n\n- **Policy Rules:**\n  1. All remote writes pass secret scan first\n  2. All local writes pass canonical path validation first\n  3. 412 conflict uses bounded retry with deterministic terminal error\n  4. Files over max-size are skipped with explicit classification\n  5. Max-entry overflow has deterministic truncation/skip policy\n\n- **Constants Classification:**\n  1. `api-types`: sync outcome enums and error class identifiers\n  2. `config`: retry caps, limits, endpoint keys\n  3. `core-domain`: invariant ordering (validate → scan → write/push)\n  4. `state-store`/`platform`: local lock/key/file internals\n  5. `ui-tui`: user-facing summaries only\n\n- **Acceptance Matrix:**\n  - Contract tests: Path traversal/symlink escape, Secret findings skip, 412 conflict retry limits\n  - Integration tests: Pull → merge → push happy path, Unauthorized token handling, Mixed payload handling\n  - Security tests: Secret scanner redaction, Write outside team root prevention, Audit events\n\n---\n\n### 2. EXISTING TEAMMEM-RELATED SOURCE FILES\n\n**Files Found:**\n\n1. **`/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/lib.rs`**\n   - Exports `pub mod teammem_kairos_service;`\n   - Contains test module references for acceptance tests\n\n2. **`/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects