t variable parsing\n\n#### **US-040 (KAIROS) Test Examples:**\n- Mode resolution determinism\n- Route precedence and slash command routing (/brief, /kairos, /channels)\n- Tool visibility filtering with policy block lists\n- Prompt composition with multiple precedence layers\n- Error handling for disabled modes\n\n#### **US-041 (Multi-Agent Orchestration) Test Examples:**\n- Parallel spawning with overlapping scope rejection\n- Concurrent spawn tracking with `AtomicUsize`\n- Mixed result status aggregation (completed/failed/cancelled)\n- Idempotent task stopping\n- Notification parsing and synthesis\n\n---\n\n### 6. CONTRACT DOCUMENTATION FILES\n\n**Located in:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/`\n\n**Files:**\n1. `bridge-mode-contract.md` - Covers Remote Control (BRIDGE_MODE / CCR)\n2. `coordinator-mode-contract.md` - Covers coordinator mode state precedence\n3. `kairos-contract.md` - Covers assistant modes (KAIROS, BRIEF, CHANNELS)\n4. `multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md` - Covers worker orchestration\n5. `teammem-contract.md` - Covers team memory sync ← **Primary for this task**\n\n**Contract Documentation Pattern:**\n- Section 1: Objective statement\n- Section 2-3: Current code evidence and Rust boundary mapping\n- Section 4: Proposed contracts (Rust sketches)\n- Section 5: Error taxonomy\n- Section 6-7: Constants classification and policy rules\n- Section 8 (or 7): Acceptance matrix with contract/integration/CLI tests\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY\n\nThe **TeamMem system** is a team memory synchronization service that handles bidirectional sync of shared memory files with:\n\n- **Security:** Path validation, secret scanning, and audit logging\n- **Resilience:** Bounded conflict retry with configurable max retries\n- **Compliance:** File size limits, entry count limits, and error determinism\n- **Architecture:** Service trait with Pull/Push/Sync operations backed by pluggable backends\n\nThe current implementation in Rust spans `crates/application/src/` with the main service in `teammem_kairos_service.rs`, type contracts in `spec_contracts.rs`, and related infrastructure distributed across domain, platform, config, and remote-runtime crates.\n\nThe acceptance test pattern used (US-037 through US-041) follows a three-layer pyramid: contract tests (determinism), integration tests (workflows), and CLI behaviour tests (user-facing semantics). No specific US-038 test file was found; the numbering maps to US-037 (bridge), US-039 (coordinator), US-040 (KAIROS), and US-041 (multi-agent)."}],"totalDurationMs":65982,"totalTokens":59220,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2379,"cache_read_input_tokens":52931,"output_tokens":3904,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2379},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
